    <text id="F3535T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Charles M. Carleton certifies that D. D. Swift is unfit for duty due to chronic
                    dysentery.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-01-23">January 23, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">North East Maryland</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Asst. Surgeon D. D. Swift of the 126 Regt. Penn. Vols. (detailed to act in the
                    91st Regt. Penn. Vols.) having applied for a certificate in which to ground an
                    application for an extension of his leave of absence given near Falmouth Va.
                    January 14th 1863 for fifteen days. I do hereby certify that I have carefully
                    examined this officer, and find that he is afflicted with Dysenteria Chronica.
                    And that in consequence thereof he is, in my opinion, unfit for duty.</p>

                <p>I further declare my belief that he will not be able to resume his duties in a
                    less time than twenty days (20) and that to move at present would greatly
                    endanger his life.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>Chas. M. Carleton<lb/> Surgeon 18th Conn. Vols</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
